<owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="#exploratoryobservation1">
  <rdf:type rdf:resource="#ExploratoryObservation"/>
  <finding rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Coffee Price Series Analysis Report (1990-2025)

This report analyzes a time series of approximately 420 coffee prices, spanning a 35-year period from 1990 to 2025, using segmentation and Singular Spectrum Analysis (SSA) to understand price behavior.

Segmentation Methodology The time series was segmented using the PELT algorithm with an RBF model to identify periods of similar price distribution. This method effectively detected shifts in the underlying price distribution, with the number of reported changes aligning well with observed density modes in the overall price plot. For analyses focused on mean shifts, L1 or L2 models would be more appropriate.

Segment Selection and Interpretation Following segmentation, individual segments, representing periods of consistent price distribution, were selected for further analysis. For illustrative purposes, the second identified segment was chosen to demonstrate the subsequent analytical steps, with segmentation information saved for future reference.

Detailed Segment Analysis (SSA) The chosen segment underwent smoothing and subsequent Singular Spectrum Analysis (SSA) to decompose its variance. The SSA results indicated that the first three eigenvalues accounted for over 90% of the variation within this segment. Specifically, the trend component was the dominant factor, explaining the majority of price movements, while seasonal components contributed only a minor portion. Visualizations of both smoothed data and SSA components are available within the analytical tool.

Conclusion and Further Analysis This analysis focused on a single segment to illustrate the methodology. A complete understanding of the entire coffee price series would require similar detailed analysis of the remaining identified segments.</finding>
  <finding_sequence rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer">1</finding_sequence>
  <exploratory_observation_type rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Data Quality Observation</exploratory_observation_type>
  <intent rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">DATA_UNDERSTANDING</intent>
</owl:NamedIndividual>

